  "post_send_verification": [
    "Record succeeded only after a fresh TaShuo screenshot shows the exact sent text in the thread.",
    "After pressing Return, the input placeholder must reappear and a fresh TaShuo screenshot must show the exact sent text in the thread.",
    "If exact text or input-cleared evidence is not verifiable, record unknown or block managed send."
  ],
  "known_gui_pitfalls": [
    "TaShuo full query tashuo may not surface the app in iOS search; use tashu, do not press a trailing space in Spotlight, and verify the 她说 app result before tapping.",
    "Home Screen or App Library page changes must use trackpad-style wheel/scroll gestures, not click-drag, because click-drag can enter edit mode.",
    "The 推荐 card like/pass/special buttons are high-risk dating actions and are not navigation.",
    "飞行 shows a map prompt to tap screen and start chat; do not tap the map/start-chat surface during autonomous observation.",
    "待回答/question-gate pages are not ordinary chat threads until the user-owned gate decision permits conversation.",
    "Question-gate replies require user confirmation and are not eligible for autonomous question-gate send.",
    "macOS pbcopy alone may not update iPhone Universal Clipboard; do not treat clipboard state as TaShuo staging evidence.",
    "If Cmd+V or paste produces a literal shortcut key such as v, an IME candidate, or any wrong text, cancel/refocus/backspace-clean it, verify the input is empty or safe, and block instead of continuing.",
    "TaShuo live send requires target-specific binding evidence. For mac-ios-app current-thread send, use current_thread_visual_identity with a fresh visual_anchor_hash; do not use message-list row position or header OCR as the binding evidence. For iPhone Mirroring row-open paths, row-to-thread structural evidence remains allowed.",
    "Emoji or otherwise non-OCR nicknames are valid targets in any message-list row; bind the intended row with chat_list_row_to_thread evidence instead of switching to an OCR-friendly conversation.",
    "Ordinary conversation classification can use the persistent bottom input toolbar and four tool buttons as page-structure evidence; exact payload verification requires text or approved visual evidence, while mac-ios-app current-thread target binding must use a visual anchor hash.",
    "For mac-ios-app task startup, use prepare-message-page: determine the top-level page from the visual bottom-tab highlight, tap the messages tab if needed, then hand off to visual message-list planning without OCR-first fallback or fixed row-coordinate thread entry.",
    "TaShuo ordinary chat sends with Return; do not plan or execute a Send-button click.",
    "Visible bubble evidence can support diagnosis but cannot replace exact verification of the payload text.",
    "Non-ABC input sources can leave app names in the iOS Spotlight candidate bar; verify the app result after typing before tapping."
  ],
